@returns {number} Number that is the sum of the value numbers.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_SUM.html | www.hcltechsw.com }
@example
REM "returns 6";
@Sum(1, 2, 3);
@example
REM "returns 11";
@Sum([1, 2, 3], [1, 4]);

@Tan.!doc:
@category:Math & Trigonometry
Given an angle in radians, returns the tangent of the angle. In a right triangle
the tangent of an acute angle is the ratio of the length of the opposite side to
the length of the adjacent side.

@param {number} angle Number or number list. An angle expressed in radians for which you want the tangent.
@returns {number} Number or number list. The tangent of angle, rounded to 15 decimal places.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TAN.html | www.hcltechsw.com }
@example
REM "returns 0.5463024898437905";
@Tan(.5);
@example
REM "returns [0.5463024898437905, 0.6841368083416923, 0.8422883804630794]";
@Tan(.5,.6,.7);

@Text.!doc:
@category:Text
Converts any value to a text string.
@param {*} value Any value you want to convert to text.
@param {TextOrTextList} [format] Up to four format strings. These determine how the text is returned.
If _value_ is already a string, _format_ is ignored. This parameter is currently not implemented.
@returns {TextOrTextList} The _value_ you specified, converted to text. If you used any format-strings, they are applied.
@see For more information see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TEXT.html|www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns "123.45"};
@Text(123.45);

@TextToNumber.!doc:
@category:Text
Converts a text string to a number, where possible.
@param {TextOrTextList} text The string you want to convert to a number. If _text_ contains both numbers and letters,
it must begin with a number to be converted properly. For example, the string "12ABC" converts to 12, but "ABC12"
produces an error.
@returns {NumberOrNumberList} The _text_, converted to a number.
@see For more information see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TEXTTONUMBER.html|www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns the number 123};
@TextToNumber("123");
@example
REM {Returns 123 : 456};
@TextToNumber("123" : "456");

@TextToTime.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Converts a text string to a Date object, where possible.

@param {TextOrTextList} time_text The string you want to convert to a Date object. "Today", "Tomorrow", and "Yesterday" are the only
legal strings to use to represent relative dates.
@returns {Date|DateRange|Error|(Date|DateRange|Error)[]} The _time_text_, converted to a time-date.
@see For more information see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TEXTTOTIME.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns Date 05/12/2023};
@TextToTime("05/12/23");
@example
REM {Returns Date for tomorrow};
@TextToTime("Tomorrow");

@ThisName.!doc:
@category:Information
Returns the name of the current field.
Only works within the context of a text/field widget within an Action formula.
Supports RichText, TextBox and TextArea.
@param {*} eventobject Optional. If the eventobject is not specified, the eventobject set by setActionEventObject is used.
@returns {string} The name of the current field.
