@Time.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Constructs and returns a Date object from one of the following combination of time-date parameters:
   ( hour, minute, second ), ( year, month, day, hour, minute, second ),
   or Date object or array of Date objects, as per the notes formula Time function parameters.

@param {*} args Date or list of Date objects. Or the numbers corresponding to the date and time components of which you want the time.
    Either all 6 date and time numbers or 3 time numbers.
@returns {TextOrTextList} Text or text list. The date string(s) corresponding to the parameters sent to @Time.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TIME.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns '4/14/1900 12:00:30 PM'};
@Time(1900; 4; 14; 12; 0; 30);
@example
REM {Returns '12:00:30 PM'};
@Time([4/14/1900 12:00:30]);
@example
REM {Returns '12:00:30 PM' if dtObj is 4/14/1900 12:00:30 PM'};
@Time(dtObj);

@TimeMerge.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Builds a time-date value from separate date, time, and time zone values.

@param {DateOrDateList} dateStr String, Date, or array of Strings or Dates. The date string or time-date object representing
    the date you want to include in the new date-time value. Must be same type as timeStr.
@param {DateOrDateList} timeStr String, Date, or array of Strings or Dates. The time string or time-date object representing
    the time you want to include in the new date-time value. Must be same type as dateStr.
@param {string} [timeZone] String. Optional. The canonical time zone value you want to apply to the new date-time value.
    You can use a Time zone field to create this value.
@returns {DateOrDateList} A new time-date value or time-date list made up of the date, time, and zone supplied as function parameters.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TIMEMERGE.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns '02/23/02 17:45:00'};
@TimeMerge([02/23/02], [17:45:00]);

@TimeToTextInZone.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Converts a time-date value to a text string, incorporating time zone information.

@param {DateOrDateList} timeDate Time-date value or time-date list. The time-date value or values to be converted.
@param {string} timeZone Canonical time zone value. You can derive a time zone value using a Notes® Time zone field.
@param {string} format Optional. String consisting of one or more format specifiers.
@returns {TextOrTextList} The time-date value converted to a string.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TIMETOTEXTINZONE.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns "02/26/2002"};
@TimeToTextInZone("02/26/2002 03:06 PM EST";"Z=9$DO=1$DL=4 1 1 10-1 1$ZX=3$ZN=Alaskan";"D2T1S3");

@TimeZoneToText.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Converts a canonical time zone value to a human-readable text string.

@param {TextOrTextList} timezone Canonical time zone value or list of time zone values. Use a Notes Time zone field to create a time zone value.
@param {string} [format] String consisting of one or more of the following format specifiers:
   - "S" : Short time zone string, for example:"GMT-08:00"
   - "A" : Alias for local time zone. For example, if the zone is the same as the zone in which the system is running, returns: "Local time"
@returns {TextOrTextList} The _timezone_ value converted to a string. If you do not include a format specifier, a long time zone label is returned.
@see For more information see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TIMEZONETOTEXT.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns "GMT-07:00"};
@TimeZoneToText("Z=7$DO=0$ZX=6$ZN=US Mountain";"S");
@example
REM {Returns "(GMT-07:00) Phoenix, Fort Nelson, Creston, Mazatlan, Hermosillo"};
@TimeZoneToText("Z=7$DO=0$ZX=6$ZN=US Mountain";"A");
@example
REM {Returns "GMT-04:30"};
@TimeZoneToText("Z=3004$DO=0$ZN=Venezuela$ZX=143";"S");
@example
REM {Returns "GMT+05:45"};
@TimeZoneToText("Z=-4505$DO=0$ZN=Nepal$ZX=177";"S");

@ToNumber.!doc:
@category:Text
Converts a value to a number.
@param {string|number|Error|(string|number|Error)[]} value Any value to convert to a number. A value that cannot be converted returns the error, "The value cannot be converted to a Number."
@returns {NumberOrNumberList} The value converted to a number.
@see For more information see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TONUMBER.html|www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns 20 : 40};
@ToNumber("20" : "40");
@example
REM {Return error "The value cannot be converted to a Number."};
@ToNumber("r");

@ToTime.!doc:
@category:Text
Converts a value with a data type of text or time to a date-time value.
@param {DateOrDateList} time_text The value to convert. A value that cannot be converted returns the error,
"The value cannot be converted to a Number."
@returns {DateOrDateList} The value converted to a date object.
@see For more information see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TOTIME.html|www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns Date values 02/29/2008 : 03/01/2008};
@ToTime("2/29/08" : "3/1/08");
@example
REM {Return Date with value returns 08/31/2021};
@Adjust(@ToTime("08/29/21");0;0;2;0;0;0);

@Today.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Returns today's date.

@returns {string} The date string for the current date.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TODAY.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns '6/7/2024' if today is June 7th, 2024};
@Today();

@Tomorrow.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Returns the time-date value that corresponds to tomorrow's date.

@returns {string} Date string for tomorrow's date.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TOMORROW.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns '6/7/2024' if today is June 6th, 2024};
@Tomorrow();

@Transform.!doc:
@category:Lists
Applies a formula to each element of a list and returns the results in a list.
@param { TextOrTextList|NumberOrNumberList|DateOrDateList} list The list to be acted upon.
@param {string} variableName The name of a variable. Use this variable in the formula to refer to the list element being acted upon.
@param {*} formula Valid formula that evaluates to a result. The remainder of &#64;Transform after the second parameter
is the formula that is applied to each element of the input list. The formula must return a value. If &#64;Nothing is returned, no element is added to the return list.
@returns The result of the transformation on the input list. The first value returned by the formula determines the data type of the list. Subsequent return values must be of the same type.
@see For more information see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TRANSFORM.html|www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns a 3-element list whose values are 2, -2, and 4};
@Transform(4:-4:16; "x";
@If(x >= 0; @Sqrt(x); -@Sqrt(@Abs(x))))
@example
REM {Returns a 2-element list whose values are 2 and 4};
OriginalList:=4:-4:16;
@If(OriginalList = @Nothing; @Nothing;
@Transform(OriginalList; "x";
@If(x >= 0; @Sqrt(x); @Nothing)))

@Trim.!doc:
@category:Text
Removes leading, trailing, and redundant spaces from a text string.
@param {TextOrTextList} text Text to trim.
@returns {TextOrTextList} The _text_, with extra spaces removed.
@see For more information see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TRIM.html|www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns "Robert Smith"};
@Trim("        Robert       Smith");

@True.!doc:
@category:Logical
Returns the number 1 (true).

@returns {number} The number 1 (true).
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_TRUE.html | www.hcltechsw.com}

@Unique.!doc:
@category:Lists
Without a parameter, returns a random, unique text value. With a parameter, removes duplicate values from a
_text_ list by returning only the first occurrence of each member of the list. &#64;Unique is case-sensitive.
@param {string[]} textList list of values
@returns If no parameter is specified, returns a random, unique text value. Otherwise, the _text_ list, with
duplicate values removed.
@see For more information see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_UNIQUE.html|www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns "red"; "green"; "blue"};
@Unique("red":"green":"blue":"green":"red");
@example
REM {Returns "red"; "green"; "blue"; "Green"};
@Unique("red":"green":"blue":"Green":"red");

@UpdateFormulaContext.!doc:
@category:Formula
Updates the context of a formula to a document currently being updated by the code.
For example, if the code accesses a new form called "Response" by using &#64;Command([Compose]:"Response",
&#64;UpdateFormulaContext switches the context of the formula to this new form. Any subsequent functions in
the code execute in the context of the Response document, not the current document.

@returns {Promise<void>} A promise that resolves when the context is updated or rejects with an error.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_UPDATEFORMULACONTEXT.html|www.hcltechsw.com }
@example
REM "This example, creates a response document to the currently selected document then populates its fname and lname fields with the values of the fname and lname fields in the current document.";
tempfname := fname;
templname := lname;
@Command([Compose];"Response");
@UpdateFormulaContext;
FIELD fname := tempfname;
FIELD lname := templname;

@UpperCase.!doc:
@category:Text
Converts the lowercase letters in the specified string to uppercase.
@param {TextOrTextList} text The string you want to convert to uppercase.
@returns {TextOrTextList} The string _text_, converted to uppercase letters.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_UPPERCASE.html|www.hcltechsw.com }
@example
REM {Returns "ROBERT T. SMITH"};
@UpperCase("Robert T. Smith");
@example
REM {Returns "ROBERT" : "SMITH"};
@UpperCase("Robert" : "Smith")

@UserIDCertificates.!doc:
@category:User Id
@willnotimplement:<strong>No plans to implement</strong>
@category User Id

@UserName.!doc:
@category:User Environment
Returns the current user name.

If the user name is hierarchical, &#64;UserName returns it in canonical format
(including the CN, OU, O, and C identifiers). To return the name in abbreviated
format (omitting those identifiers), use &#64;V3UserName.
@param {number} [index=0] Number. Optional. Indicating the index of user names.
0 is for primary name and 1 is for the alternate name. If this parameter is omitted, @UserName returns the primary name.
@returns {Promise<string>} Promise that resolves to the current user name.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_USERNAME.html|www.hcltechsw.com }

@V3UserName.!doc:
@category:User Environment
Returns the current user name or server name. Using &#64;V3UserName on a local
database or in a private view in a server-based database returns the user's name.

If the user name is hierarchical, &#64;V3UserName returns the name in
abbreviated format (omitting the CN, OU, O, and C identifiers). To return the
name in canonical format, use &#64;UserName.
@returns Promise that resolves to the current user name or server name.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_V3USERNAME.html|www.hcltechsw.com }

@Weekday.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Extracts the day of the week from a date; if text, uses current locale to convert to a date.
Returns a number that identifies the day.

@param {DateOrDateList} dateOrDateList The date, as a string, Date object, or Array of Date objects or strings, of the day you are trying to find.
@returns {NumberOrNumberList} The day of the week of a given date as a number from 1 through 7. (default)
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_WEEKDAY.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns 4};
@Weekday(@Date(1900; 0; 31));
@example
REM {Returns [2, 3]};
@Weekday(@Date(95; 11; 20; 8; 58; 12) : @Date(95; 11; 21; 8; 58; 12));

@While.!doc:
@category:Logical
Executes one or more statements iteratively while a condition is true. Checks the condition before executing the statements.
No plans to implement - Convert to Native JS

@see For further information, see &nbsp;{@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_WHILE_FUNCTION.html | www.hcltechsw.com}

@Wide.!doc:
@category:Text
Converts half-pitch alphanumeric characters (single-byte characters -- SBCS) in the specified
string to full-pitch alphanumeric characters (double-byte characters -- DBCS). This function
works in Japanese, Korean, Simplified Chinese, and traditional Chinese environments. In the
Japanese environment, this function can convert half-pitch Katakana as well.
@param {TextOrTextList} text The string you want to convert to double-byte characters.
@returns {TextOrTextList} The string converted to double-byte characters.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_WIDE_4116.html|www.hcltechsw.com }
@example
REM {Returns "New York" as full-pitch characters, to save space for displaying the string};
@Wide("New York");

@WindowMaximize.!doc:
@category:Window
Maximizes the current application window.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_WINDOWMAXIMIZE.html | hcltechsw.com}

@WindowMinimize.!doc:
@category:Window
Minimizes the current application window.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_WINDOWMINIMIZE.html | hcltechsw.com}

@Word.!doc:
@category:Text
Returns the specified word from a text string. A "word" is defined as the part of a string that
is delimited by the defined separator character. For example, if you specify a space (" ") as
the separator, then a word is any series of characters preceded by and followed by a space
(or the beginning or end of the string).
@param {TextOrTextList} text  The string you want to scan.
@param {string} separator The character that you want used to delimit a word in the string.
@param {number} number A position indicating which word you want returned from string. A positive number
refers to the position of the word starting from the beginning where 1 is the first word. A
negative number refers to the position of the word starting from the end where -1 is the last word.
@returns {TextOrTextList} The word that holds the position specified by the number in the string; for example,
if number is 3, returns the third word in the string. If a text list is used, returns
(in list format) a word from each list that holds the specified position. Returns an empty string
if number is out of range, except that 0 is equivalent to 1.
@see For further information, see &nbsp;{@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_WIDE_4116.html|www.hcltechsw.com }
@example
REM {Returns "Collins,"};
@Word("Larson, Collins, and Jensen"; " " ; 2);
@example
REM {Returns "M."};
@Word("Larson,James,M.";",";3);

@Year.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Extracts the year from the specified date.

@param {DateOrDateList} dateOrDateList The date, as a string, Date object, or Array of Date objects or strings, of the year you are trying to find.
@returns {NumberOrNumberList} Number or number list. The number corresponding to the year.
    Returns -1 if the time-date provided contains only a time value and not a date.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_YEAR.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns 1900};
@Year(@Date(1900; 0; 1));

@Yes.!doc:
@category:Logical
Returns the number 1 (true).

@returns {number} The number 1 (true).
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_YES.html | www.hcltechsw.com}

@Yesterday.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Returns the time-date value that corresponds to yesterday's date.

@returns {string} Date string. Yesterday's date.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_YESTERDAY.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns '6/5/2024' if today is June 6th, 2024};
@Yesterday();

@Zone.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Returns the time zone setting of the current computer or of a time-date value,
and indicates if daylight-saving time is observed.
The time zone is represented as the number of hours that must be added to the
time-date to convert it to Greenwich Mean Time.

@param {DateOrDateList} dateOrDateList Date or date list. Optional. The date whose zone you want to know.
    You must specify both a date; otherwise, @Zone returns 0.
@returns {NumberOrNumberList} Number or number list. The time zone, followed by a period, followed by a flag indicating daylight-saving time.
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_ZONE.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns 5 (if in EST)};
@Zone([1/26/94 11:00 AM]);

@Date.!doc:
@category:Date & Time
Constructs the date from year, month, and day of month or translates numbers for the various components of time and date,
then returns the time-date value.

@param {DateOrDateList} yearOrDateTime The year that you want to appear in the resulting date.
    You must specify an entire four-digit year. (For example, use 1996, not 96). Or Date object or list of Date objects.
@param {number} month Optional (when DateTime provided). The month that you want to appear in the resulting date. (For example, use 1 to specify January).
@param {number} day Optional (when DateTime provided). The day that you want to appear in the resulting date.
@param {number} hour Optional. The number of hours. This value will be truncated from the resulting date.
@param {number} minute Optional. The number of minutes. This value will be truncated from the resulting date.
@param {number} second Optional. The number of seconds. This value will be truncated from the resulting date.
@returns {DateOrDateList} The date and time of the given year, month, and day
@see For further information, see {@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_DATE.html | www.hcltechsw.com}
@example
REM {Returns '4/14/1900 12:00:30 PM'};
@Date(1900; 4; 14; 12; 0; 30);
@example
REM {Returns '12/12/1912'};
@Date(12; 12; 12);
@example
REM {Returns '4/14/1900' if dtObj is 4/14/1900 12:00:30 PM'};
@Date(dtObj);

